    "title": "Oil price agency Platts posts lower adjusted operating profit",
    "locations": [],
    "highlightText": "",
    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "April 26 (Reuters) - Oil price agency Platts, a unit of S&P Global Inc, posted a 4 percent decline in first-quarter adjusted operating profit on Thursday, hurt by lower trading volumes.\nRevenue at Platts, however, increased 3 percent to $196 million in the quarter ended March 31, helped by growth its core subscription business.\nRevenue growth was partially offset by a decline in its Global Trading Services business as reduced volatility in key commodity products led to lower trading volumes.\nAdjusted operating profit fell to $95 million from $98 million a year ago. (Reporting by Radhika Rukmangadhan in Bengaluru Editing by Saumyadeb Chakrabarty)\n ",
